- edit the key

  ``` bash
  gpg --edit-key YOUR_KEY_ID
  ```

- inside gpg prompt

  ``` bash
  gpg> adduid
  Real name: Savolla
  Email address: newemail@example.com
  Comment:
  ```

- confirm

- set the new uid as primary

  ``` bash
  gpg> uid 2          # select the new uid by number
  gpg> primary        # make it primary
  ```

- optionally delete the old uid

  ``` bash
  gpg> uid 1          # select old uid
  gpg> deluid         # delete it
  ```

- save

  ``` bash
  gpg> save
  ```
